00:02:03,031 --> 00:02:05,090
CHAPTER I:
By motor- scooter.

2
00:02:06,230 --> 00:02:21,628
Dear Diary,
there's something I like to do very much!

3
00:02:22,573 --> 00:02:25,347
(MUSIC)

4
00:04:01,620 --> 00:04:04,657
<i>Moretti: In Rome, the cinemas
are closed for the summer,</i>

5
00:04:05,340 --> 00:04:08,776
<i>or at least they show such films as
"Sex love and sheep",</i>

6
00:04:09,940 --> 00:04:14,377
<i>"Beastly desires",
"Snow white and the seven black dwarves",</i>

7
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:18,858
<i>horror films like "Henry",</i>

8
00:04:20,180 --> 00:04:22,767
<i>or a few Italian films.</i>

9
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:26,253
<i>(Man #1 in a film): I am a little afraid
to come back into play.</i>

10
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:27,978
<i>I am a coward.</i>

11
00:04:28,266 --> 00:04:31,057
<i>What has happened
in these years, I wonder...</i>

12
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:32,859
<i>I don't know it anymore.</i>

13
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:35,620
<i>(Man #2) Hair is getting grey,</i>

14
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:37,577
<i>(Man #3) and defeats
begin to be a burden.</i>

15
00:04:37,660 --> 00:04:39,412
...a non-stop series of defeats.

16
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:42,219
Our generation...
What's become of us?

17
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:46,015
Advertisers, architects, stock agents,
deputies, aldermen..

18
00:04:46,180 --> 00:04:47,408
...journalists.

19
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:50,652
We have changed, we're worse,

20
00:04:51,980 --> 00:04:53,857
nowadays we're all accomplices.

21
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:56,535
But why this obsession?

22
00:04:56,700 --> 00:05:00,534
"All equal, all compromised,
we're all accomplices"...

23
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:03,009
Can you tell me when
we last had a walk together?

24
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:05,250
We are together
only from force of habit.

25
00:05:05,420 --> 00:05:06,933
You're ashamed of me.

26
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:10,894
What a headache, even
"Optalidon" is no longer the same.

27
00:05:11,660 --> 00:05:14,777
Remember how reassuring
its old tube used to be?

28
00:05:14,860 --> 00:05:17,328
Everything is different now.

29
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:20,470
You know, Antonio?
You're getting worse and worse.

30
00:05:20,670 --> 00:05:22,694
You can no longer feel
anything real now.

31
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:26,409
We are old, we're soured,
we are dishonest in our jobs.

32
00:05:26,620 --> 00:05:29,930
We used to shout horrendous,
violent things, in our marches

33
00:05:30,140 --> 00:05:32,654
and now look
how ugly we got.

34
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:36,216
<i>Moretti: YOU used to shout
horrendous and violent things</i>

35
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:38,411
<i>and you got ugly.</i>

36
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:40,532
<i>I used to shout true things,</i>

37
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:44,019
<i>and now I'm a wonderful 40 year old man.</i>

38
00:06:16,060 --> 00:06:19,336
<i>What I like the most
is to see the houses,</i>

39
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:20,899
<i>to see the districts,</i>

40
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:24,769
<i>and the district that I prefer
is the Garbatella.</i>

41
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:29,022
<i>I walk around
the council houses there.</i>

42
00:06:55,660 --> 00:06:59,170
<i>However I don't like to see
the houses only from the outside,</i>

43
00:06:59,340 --> 00:07:02,855
<i>Sometimes I like to see
what they look like inside too.</i>

44
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:08,294
<i>Therefore, I ring some bell
and say I need to check the place</i>

45
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,837
<i>because I am preparing a film.</i>

46
00:07:11,037 --> 00:07:15,360
<i>The landlords usually ask me:
"What's this film about?"</i>

47
00:07:15,780 --> 00:07:17,816
<i>and I never know what to say.</i>

48
00:07:18,060 --> 00:07:22,372
This film is the story
of a Trotskian confectioner

49
00:07:23,660 --> 00:07:27,972
and it's set in Italy in the '50s.
It's a musical.

50
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:30,139
A musical.

51
00:07:30,374 --> 00:07:34,916
<i>Moretti: By the way, a musical about
a Trotskian confectioner wouldn't be bad at all,</i>

52
00:07:35,116 --> 00:07:38,154
<i>above all if set in the
conformist Italy of the '50s.</i>

53
00:07:41,580 --> 00:07:46,081
<i>When I ride my motor scooter,
I also like to stop and watch the attics</i>

54
00:07:46,281 --> 00:07:47,976
<i>where I would like to live.</i>

55
00:07:48,180 --> 00:07:50,978
<i>I imagine myself renovating the apartments</i>

56
00:07:51,140 --> 00:07:53,495
<i>high above, those that I see
from the road,</i>

57
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:58,745
<i>apartments whose owners
have no intention to sell.</i>

58
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:03,331
<i>One day I saw an attic
that seemed to me more accessible.</i>

59
00:08:03,540 --> 00:08:07,443
<i>Silvia and I also went to check it.</i>

60
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,491
<i>We asked how much it cost,</i>

61
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:13,190
<i>and the answer was:
"Ten million lire per square meter".</i>

62
00:08:13,348 --> 00:08:15,057
<i>How, "Ten million lire per square meter"?</i>

63
00:08:15,140 --> 00:08:18,132
<i>He says, "Well, of course,</i>

64
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:21,770
<i>because Dandolo Rd.
is a historical road.</i>

65
00:08:22,020 --> 00:08:24,693
<i>Garibaldi fought the Resistance here.</i>

66
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:29,973
<i>I don't know why, I don't get it,
maybe I'm sick,</i>

67
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,857
<i>but I love this bridge.</i>

68
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:35,648
<i>I have to come here
at least twice a day.</i>

69
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:10,774
Want to know what I was thinking of?
A very sad thing.

70
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:16,305
That I, even in a more decent
society than this one,

71
00:09:16,405 --> 00:09:19,113
will always be in the minority,

72
00:09:19,313 --> 00:09:21,856
but not as in those films where
there are a man and a woman

73
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:24,739
who hate one another and tear
each other to pieces on a desert island

74
00:09:24,820 --> 00:09:27,015
because the director of the film
doesn't believe in people.

75
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:28,419
I believe in people.

76
00:09:28,580 --> 00:09:30,969
I don't believe
in the majority of people.

77
00:09:31,060 --> 00:09:33,210
I'm afraid that
I will always be comfortable

78
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:34,449
only in the minority.

79
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:36,610
Whatever, good luck.

80
00:09:41,180 --> 00:09:47,214
<i>Moretti: Actually, I've always dreamt
of being able to dance.</i>

81
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:51,654
<i>"Flashdance", that film was called...</i>

82
00:09:51,854 --> 00:09:54,456
<i>It changed my life forever.</i>

83
00:09:54,700 --> 00:10:00,335
<i>A film on the dance,
on learning to dance,</i>

84
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:03,691
<i>while all I can do is watch,</i>

85
00:10:03,780 --> 00:10:07,937
<i>which is also nice,
but it's a completely different thing.</i>

86
00:10:09,072 --> 00:10:11,084
(LATIN-AMERICAN MUSIC)

87
00:11:58,420 --> 00:12:00,297
Want to know what my dream is?

88
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:03,298
My dream has always been
to learn how to dance.

89
00:12:03,380 --> 00:12:06,611
I haven't been the same anymore,
after watching that film

90
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:09,009
"Flashdance", with Jennifer Beals.

91
00:12:09,220 --> 00:12:12,053
Is that dancer down there
Jennifer Beals?

92
00:12:12,260 --> 00:12:13,010
No.

93
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:15,894
I envy them so much!
Are you Jennifer Beals?

94
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:16,856
No.

95
00:12:48,180 --> 00:12:51,650
<i>Moretti: Spinaceto, a district
which has been built recently.</i>

96
00:12:52,380 --> 00:12:55,736
<i>One never names it
but to say bad things about it.</i>

97
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:58,454
<i>"Alright, but we aren't
in Spinaceto here!"</i>

98
00:12:58,620 --> 00:13:01,054
<i>"But where do you live?
In Spinaceto?".</i>

99
00:13:01,260 --> 00:13:04,377
<i>I remember
that once I even read a script</i>

100
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:08,094
<i>called:
"Escape from Spinaceto".</i>

101
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:11,769
<i>It was about a boy
who escaped from his district and from home</i>

102
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:13,578
<i>...and never came back.</i>

103
00:13:13,820 --> 00:13:17,559
<i>And so, let's go
to Spinaceto.</i>

104
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:34,371
I thought that
Spinaceto was worse.

105
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:37,510
- But it's not bad at all. Bye.
- You're right, I was...

106
00:13:37,710 --> 00:13:39,262
Bye.

107
00:13:46,620 --> 00:13:49,134
(ARABIC MUSIC)

108
00:14:20,980 --> 00:14:24,450
<i>Moretti: Casalpalocco.
Passing by these houses,</i>

109
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:29,039
<i>I smell the odour of the tracksuits
which are worn here instead of the suits,</i>

110
00:14:29,239 --> 00:14:33,502
<i>...of videotapes and watchdogs
in the gardens</i>

111
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:37,704
<i>and precooked pizzas
in their cardboard boxes.</i>

112
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:43,189
<i>But why did they come here
thirty years ago?</i>

113
00:14:48,780 --> 00:14:50,008
Excuse me!

114
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:52,734
Why did you
come to live here?

115
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:54,532
But look how green,
how calm here is.

116
00:14:54,732 --> 00:14:57,253
It's green, but I'm sure
that you came here...

117
00:14:57,340 --> 00:14:58,568
...30 years ago. In 1961?

118
00:14:58,780 --> 00:15:00,054
'62.

119
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:03,019
Thirty years ago Rome
was a beautiful town...

120
00:15:03,220 --> 00:15:04,494
But here is different.

121
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:07,976
Yes, is it different,
but Rome was beautiful, understand?

122
00:15:08,180 --> 00:15:11,377
That's what frightens me:
dogs behind the gates,

123
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:14,018
videotapes, slippers...

124
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:30,378
Jennifer Beals?

125
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:33,893
Jennifer Beals? Jennifer Beals?

126
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,376
- Jennifer Beals?
- Yes?

127
00:15:35,576 --> 00:15:36,790
- Of "Flashdance"?
- Yes.

128
00:15:36,990 --> 00:15:38,832
- Who's this guy?
- I don't know.

129
00:15:39,032 --> 00:15:39,841
What has he said?

130
00:15:40,041 --> 00:15:41,198
"Who are you".

131
00:15:41,398 --> 00:15:45,689
You know,
I wish I could dance...

132
00:15:45,889 --> 00:15:47,058
(JENNIFER BEALS TRANSLATES
INTO ENGLISH)

133
00:15:47,140 --> 00:15:50,177
But if I lived
in Emilia Romagna..

134
00:15:50,420 --> 00:15:53,856
where centres for the elderly,
and hospitals which work are,

135
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:56,215
and structures, services,
and schools of dance,

136
00:15:56,380 --> 00:15:58,735
...tango, merengue,
cha- cha, mambo..

137
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:02,336
when I listen to the music
I would dance,

138
00:16:02,740 --> 00:16:04,458
instead of watching others dance.

139
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:07,656
Those shoes
look very comfortable,

140
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:11,893
so simple and yet...
they must be comfortable.

141
00:16:12,140 --> 00:16:14,510
Yes, very much.

142
00:16:14,820 --> 00:16:18,290
I think this guy must be,
you know, a feet maniac.

143
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:19,443
Then let's go.

144
00:16:19,643 --> 00:16:21,928
No, you just have to be calm,
he's just a little off. Just, you know...

145
00:16:22,128 --> 00:16:23,978
What have you said? Crazy?

146
00:16:24,180 --> 00:16:25,504
No, no.

147
00:16:25,704 --> 00:16:26,669
Wasn't it "crazy"?

148
00:16:26,869 --> 00:16:29,056
No, I have said "off".

149
00:16:29,256 --> 00:16:30,798
And what does it mean?

150
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:37,965
It means "special", "peculiar",
almost crazy, but not crazy yet.

151
00:16:38,860 --> 00:16:45,062
Isn't it right? I mean, off
is not really crazy, not really troubled.

152
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:48,252
Ah, you mean like
off-centre.

153
00:16:48,532 --> 00:16:50,172
Yeah, like off-centre, but...

154
00:16:50,660 --> 00:16:57,517
Something more precise,
maybe "whimsical".

155
00:16:57,740 --> 00:16:59,412
Whimsical?

156
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:02,566
Almost stupid.

157
00:17:05,060 --> 00:17:08,973
<i>Moretti: Also when I'm in other cities,
the only thing that I like to do</i>

158
00:17:09,180 --> 00:17:10,932
<i>is look at the houses.</i>

159
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:14,880
<i>Moretti: How beautiful
a film about houses would be...</i>

160
00:17:14,940 --> 00:17:16,737
<i>"A view on the houses".</i>

161
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:20,019
<i>Garbatella, 1927.</i>

162
00:17:24,660 --> 00:17:27,618
<i>Villaggio Olimpico, 1960.</i>

