173
00:19:50,620 --> 00:19:53,925
<i>Moretti: I wander about for a while</i>

174
00:19:53,980 --> 00:19:58,512
<i>trying to remember
who told me this film was good.</i>

175
00:19:58,712 --> 00:20:02,415
<i>I had read
a review in a paper,</i>

176
00:20:02,580 --> 00:20:05,300
<i>something positive on "Henry".</i>

177
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:10,192
<i>Suddenly I remember
and find that article,</i>

178
00:20:10,340 --> 00:20:14,274
<i>and I want to copy it
to my diary. Here it is:</i>

179
00:20:14,420 --> 00:20:18,513
<i>..."Henry kills people,
but he's almost a good person,</i>

180
00:20:18,780 --> 00:20:21,493
<i>"he doesn't speak much,
he'd rather act.</i>

181
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:24,572
<i>"His friend Otis
is a pig instead.</i>

182
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:27,857
<i>"Henry is solid for his victims,</i>

183
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:30,047
<i>"he's the blue-blooded prince
of annihilation,</i>

184
00:20:30,247 --> 00:20:32,516
<i>"and promises them
a compassionate death. Otis doesn't.</i>

185
00:20:32,716 --> 00:20:35,213
<i>"The director
pushes the audience</i>

186
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:39,213
<i>"into an even worse kind of nightmare,
with a final shower of splatter.</i>

187
00:20:39,380 --> 00:20:42,736
<i>"Pierced Eyes,
tortured flesh, abomination.</i>

188
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:46,876
<i>"Henry is perhaps
the first to scorn</i>

189
00:20:47,076 --> 00:20:51,124
<i>"the criminal philosophy
of the lombrosianis in Hollywood.</i>

190
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:57,461
<i>I wonder, those
who write such things,</i>

191
00:20:58,701 --> 00:21:05,892
<i>at night, before sleeping,
aren't they a little ashamed?</i>

192
00:21:08,944 --> 00:21:12,611
Moretti: But when did it all start?

193
00:21:12,820 --> 00:21:14,655
I don't know, I don't know.

194
00:21:14,855 --> 00:21:17,090
Perhaps
when you wrote:

195
00:21:17,260 --> 00:21:20,252
..."That Korean film
was a melodrama in dress,

196
00:21:20,460 --> 00:21:23,258
"where clothes,
and above all hats, were delirious.

197
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:26,332
"Super feminist, flaming
and demoniac"?

198
00:21:26,540 --> 00:21:28,895
"Shot like a trip
by a Spielberg-like director

199
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:31,892
"who got into futurist
spaces and rhythms.

200
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:35,013
And then there's
Cronenberg's "Naked Lunch",

201
00:21:35,220 --> 00:21:38,912
"(shouting) Pure high budgeted
underground pus...

202
00:21:39,112 --> 00:21:41,326
- Enough! Enough!
- "A true cult movie!

203
00:21:41,540 --> 00:21:44,737
"Women are not better
for Jonathan Demme,

204
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:49,456
..."at least they are like Lin Piao's
proletarians or sub proletarians

205
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:51,537
"of the three circling worlds,

206
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:57,531
"but certainly, his women
succeed in bearing the war

207
00:21:57,700 --> 00:22:01,701
"at the imaginary department
for surgical operations.

208
00:22:01,901 --> 00:22:05,893
"And in fact, before Lula and Sailor
hold each other in the happy end,

209
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:10,934
..."whispering "love me tender",
Sailor will spend a few years in prison,

210
00:22:11,180 --> 00:22:13,535
"shattered heads will fly,

211
00:22:13,780 --> 00:22:16,692
"stray dogs will catch
chopped off hands,

212
00:22:16,940 --> 00:22:22,563
"and smoke hundreds of Kools,
Merits and Marlboros, showing off.

213
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:41,858
<i>I don't know why,
but I had never been</i>

214
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:44,515
<i>where Pasolini was killed, before.</i>

215
00:22:48,420 --> 00:22:50,331
(MUSIC)

216
00:27:32,179 --> 00:27:34,224
CHAPTER II:
Islands.

217
00:27:51,900 --> 00:27:54,530
<i>Moretti: We're almost in Lipari.</i>

218
00:27:54,700 --> 00:27:58,613
<i>I'm going to see a friend
who retired there eleven years ago.</i>

219
00:27:58,980 --> 00:28:02,529
<i>He has only studied
Joyce's 'Ulysses" since then.</i>

220
00:28:03,980 --> 00:28:06,858
<i>I have to start writing my film</i>

221
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:11,773
<i>and I have the notes
I need for the job with me.</i>

222
00:28:12,340 --> 00:28:15,031
<i>I've had them for years.</i>

223
00:28:17,020 --> 00:28:21,254
<i>I am sure that
I'll do something good in Lipari.</i>

224
00:28:28,734 --> 00:28:31,298
(HORNS)
(TRAFFIC ROAR)

