01:27:11,746 --> 01:27:14,214
(THE PHYSICIAN EXPLAINS IN CHINESE)

931
01:27:16,706 --> 01:27:20,494
The doctor would like to know
if you had any sexual excess last year.

932
01:27:21,117 --> 01:27:22,092
No.

933
01:27:40,026 --> 01:27:41,220
<i>Moretti: Ouch.</i>

934
01:27:41,466 --> 01:27:43,622
<i>- Dr. Yang: Does it hurt?
- Moretti: A little.</i>

935
01:28:00,226 --> 01:28:02,615
These are the last two, eh.

936
01:28:03,106 --> 01:28:03,982
Yes.

937
01:28:11,466 --> 01:28:13,292
Here, good.

938
01:28:23,386 --> 01:28:26,856
<i>Moretti: Doctor Yang
leaves me alone in the room.</i>

939
01:28:28,666 --> 01:28:31,100
<i>He leaves me alone
for a quarter of an hour</i>

940
01:28:31,386 --> 01:28:34,064
<i>and I fall a little asleep too.</i>

941
01:28:34,306 --> 01:28:37,142
<i>Then he returns all of a sudden.</i>

942
01:28:37,386 --> 01:28:39,058
(FOOTSTEPS OF DR. YANG)

943
01:28:39,266 --> 01:28:40,255
How are you?

944
01:28:40,426 --> 01:28:41,302
Fine.

945
01:28:50,346 --> 01:28:52,177
<i>Can you feel the heat?</i>

946
01:28:52,386 --> 01:28:53,936
<i>Yes.</i>

947
01:28:57,506 --> 01:28:59,383
(MUSIC)

948
01:29:35,346 --> 01:29:38,702
<i>Moretti: So far, the acupuncture
hasn't helped either my itching,</i>

949
01:29:38,906 --> 01:29:40,385
<i>or my insomnia.</i>

950
01:29:40,626 --> 01:29:43,663
<i>But everyone is kind
at the Chinese centre,</i>

951
01:29:43,986 --> 01:29:49,139
<i>the atmosphere is nice
and so I make other attempts.</i>

952
01:29:52,466 --> 01:29:54,980
<i>Dr. Yang: Grab it well,
strong, this way.</i>

953
01:29:55,986 --> 01:29:57,624
(MORETTI COUGHS)

954
01:30:05,546 --> 01:30:06,979
How are you?

955
01:30:07,146 --> 01:30:08,056
Fine.

956
01:30:12,106 --> 01:30:13,141
Does it hurt?

957
01:30:13,266 --> 01:30:14,016
Yes.

958
01:30:20,466 --> 01:30:21,899
Can I increase it?

959
01:30:22,066 --> 01:30:22,816
Yes.

960
01:30:27,866 --> 01:30:31,905
<i>Moretti: To take care of my itch
they give me electric acupuncture</i>

961
01:30:32,866 --> 01:30:36,812
<i>with a tool called:
"needle of the flower of the plum tree".</i>

962
01:30:37,546 --> 01:30:39,901
<i>But Dr. Yang hears me cough</i>

963
01:30:40,106 --> 01:30:42,461
<i>and says that this cure
is not good.</i>

964
01:30:43,186 --> 01:30:47,576
<i>He thinks the best thing
is to have my chest x-rayed.</i>

965
01:30:47,786 --> 01:30:50,380
<i>Radiologist: Put off your jacket.</i>

966
01:30:51,106 --> 01:30:52,824
Also the T-shirt?

967
01:30:53,106 --> 01:30:56,576
<i>No, only the jacket
because there are buttons.</i>

968
01:30:59,306 --> 01:31:02,654
<i>You have to hug this.</i>

969
01:31:02,854 --> 01:31:05,067
Chin up, just a little.

970
01:31:12,906 --> 01:31:16,340
Take a breath and hold it.

971
01:31:16,546 --> 01:31:18,935
Stop, without breathing.

972
01:31:20,026 --> 01:31:24,136
<i>Moretti: The technician develops
the plate immediately.</i>

973
01:31:25,106 --> 01:31:27,779
<i>He talks to Silvia,
says that there is something</i>

974
01:31:27,986 --> 01:31:33,523
<i>around my lung, a mass,
and advises me for a CAT.</i>

975
01:31:41,506 --> 01:31:43,019
Does it taste bad?

976
01:31:43,626 --> 01:31:44,979
No, it tastes like anise.

977
01:31:45,186 --> 01:31:46,585
Okay then.

978
01:31:51,066 --> 01:31:54,216
<i>Radiologist: Stop, don't breathe.
Stop.</i>

979
01:31:59,906 --> 01:32:01,703
<i>Breathe.</i>

980
01:32:03,706 --> 01:32:06,061
<i>Don't breathe, stop.</i>

981
01:32:11,906 --> 01:32:13,703
<i>Breath.</i>

982
01:32:17,026 --> 01:32:19,540
<i>Stop, don't breathe.
Stop.</i>

983
01:32:23,946 --> 01:32:25,743
<i>Breathe.</i>

984
01:32:26,106 --> 01:32:28,540
<i>Moretti: During the CAT
to my head</i>

985
01:32:28,826 --> 01:32:32,017
<i>the radiologist looks
at the CAT to my chest</i>

986
01:32:32,466 --> 01:32:35,129
<i>and talks to Silvia and Angelo of it.</i>

987
01:32:35,186 --> 01:32:38,656
<i>He says that, according to him,
I have a sarcoma in my lungs.</i>

988
01:32:38,906 --> 01:32:41,545
<i>They ask him
for what it is and he answers</i>

989
01:32:41,746 --> 01:32:43,577
<i>that it's lung cancer.</i>

990
01:32:43,746 --> 01:32:48,965
<i>He says that, according to him,
there is no cure.</i>

991
01:32:50,826 --> 01:32:54,660
Oh, luckily the radiologist
was wrong.

992
01:32:55,706 --> 01:32:58,459
I was operated two days
after the CAT.

993
01:32:59,146 --> 01:33:00,704
My doctor friend

994
01:33:00,786 --> 01:33:03,425
to whom I had asked
to be present to the operation,

995
01:33:03,506 --> 01:33:07,419
later told me that the surgeon,
looking in a slide

996
01:33:07,866 --> 01:33:11,415
and watching a bit of the stuff
he had just removed from my lungs, said:

997
01:33:12,306 --> 01:33:16,015
..."I bet a testicle that this is
Hodgkin's lymphoma."

998
01:33:16,626 --> 01:33:18,423
"Not both, but a testicle yes".

999
01:33:19,106 --> 01:33:22,735
Hodgkin's lymphoma is a tumour
to the lymphatic system,

1000
01:33:23,626 --> 01:33:25,503
a curable tumour.

1001
01:33:26,786 --> 01:33:33,513
Then, one day, at home, I skim through
"The Garzanti Medical Encyclopaedia",

1002
01:33:33,666 --> 01:33:36,180
and checking "lymphoma", I read:

1003
01:33:37,346 --> 01:33:41,817
...symptoms are: itch,
loss of weight, perspiration.

1004
01:33:43,026 --> 01:33:50,159
However I learned something
from this story, maybe two.

1005
01:33:50,746 --> 01:33:58,388
The first is that physicians know
how to speak but they don't know how to listen..

1006
01:33:58,588 --> 01:34:07,551
...and now I am surrounded by all
the useless medicine that I have bought.

1007
01:34:08,346 --> 01:34:12,976
The second thing that I have learned
is that in the morning,

1008
01:34:13,706 --> 01:34:18,184
before breakfast, to drink
a glass of water is a good thing.

1009
01:34:18,306 --> 01:34:22,219
I was told it's good for the kidneys,
or for something else.

1010
01:34:22,506 --> 01:34:24,019
In short, it's good.

1011
01:34:26,066 --> 01:34:30,585
Then, please, milk with a dash of coffee
and a croissant...

1012
01:34:30,706 --> 01:34:33,242
...and a glass of water.


